This paper is primarily focused on the analysis of deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) for face identification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the neural tuning analogy and the use of ensembles, which are relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the representation of meaning in high-dimensional spaces, which is relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of face images, which is relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
